PAARL - Taxi-related violence in Paarl in the Western Cape is escalating despite Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula's efforts to curb local feuds. Seven taxi operators and drivers were gunned down over the past few months. READ: Government blamed for taxi violence Spokesperson Ayanda Alli-Payne says while the minister respects the independence of the taxi industry, this escalation of violence cannot be allowed to continue. Alli-Payne said the minister must step in if commuters' safety is compromised including providing alternative transportation if needed.